f=Executive Office/vista/marketplace/okr-quality-checker/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "okr-quality-checker" skill (English version), selected fulfill catalog's "okr-framework" slot vista Google OKR methodology: scoring 0.0-1.0, 0.7 success calibration, transparent grading. Chosen over broader "okr-design" (rampstackco) candidate because skill grades/validates OKRs without designing them, keeping clean boundary marcus's okr-cascade (which CREATES OKRs vista VERIFIES SCORES them). KNOWN GAP, flagged selection: catalog entry mentions "cadence" (review rhythm); skill cover review cadence. cadence discipline needed later, extend custom skill (candidate source: rampstackco okr-design's scoring-discipline review-cadence sections) rather editing copy. NOTE SOURCE CAPTURE: GitHub raw access unavailable copy time; content captured full skillsmp.com page render SKILL.md (same content, served marketplace). source's "Target Agents" section references home repo's agents (okr-designer, strategy-reviewer) kept verbatim copy-without-cutting rule; system read them "marcus (creates OKRs)" "vista (verifies them)". --> · h2:OKR Quality Checker=skill enhances OKR quality verification okr-designer strategy-reviewer. · h3:Target Agents=**okr-designer** Self-verifies quality designed OKRs, **strategy-reviewer** Confirms strategic alignment OKRs · h3:Objective Quality Criteria (QSIM)=\| Criterion       \| Description                      \| Pass Condition                     \| · h3:Objective Quality Criteria (QSIM)=\| --------------- \| -------------------------------- \| ---------------------------------- \| · h3:Objective Quality Criteria (QSIM)=\| **Q**ualitative \| Is it qualitative and inspiring? \| Provides direction without numbers \| · h3:Objective Quality Criteria (QSIM)=\| **S**trategic   \| Is it connected to strategy?     \| Clear link to higher-level goals   \| · h3:Objective Quality Criteria (QSIM)=\| **I**nspiring   \| Does it motivate the team?       \| Challenging yet achievable         \| · h3:Objective Quality Criteria (QSIM)=\| **M**emorable   \| Is it easy to remember?          \| One sentence, clear language       \| · h4:Objective BAD vs GOOD=`BAD: \· "Increase revenue" → Too vague \· "Achieve NPS score of 70" → This is a KR, not an O \· "Stabilize systems" → Not inspiring \· ` · h3:Key Result Quality Criteria (SMART-V)=\| Criterion      \| Description              \| Pass Condition                        \| · h3:Key Result Quality Criteria (SMART-V)=\| -------------- \| ------------------------ \| ------------------------------------- \| · h3:Key Result Quality Criteria (SMART-V)=\| **S**pecific   \| Is it specific?          \| What, where, how                      \| · h3:Key Result Quality Criteria (SMART-V)=\| **M**easurable \| Is it measurable?        \| Expressed numerically                 \| · h3:Key Result Quality Criteria (SMART-V)=\| **A**chievable \| Is it achievable?        \| 60-70% probability of achievement     \| · h3:Key Result Quality Criteria (SMART-V)=\| **R**elevant   \| Is it relevant to the O? \| Directly contributes to O achievement \| · h3:Key Result Quality Criteria (SMART-V)=\| **T**ime-bound \| Does it have a deadline? \| Quarterly/semi-annual cadence         \| · h3:Key Result Quality Criteria (SMART-V)=\| **V**erifiable \| Is it verifiable?        \| Data source exists                    \| · h4:KR Types=`1. Metric-based: "Improve NPS score from 40 to 60" \· 2. Milestone-based: "Complete MVP launch" \· 3. Binary: "Obtain ISO certification" (avoid when possible) \·  \· Recommended ratio: Metric 70%, Milestone 30%, Binary 0%` · h4:KR BAD vs GOOD=`BAD: \· "Improve customer satisfaction" → Not measurable \· "Zero bugs" → Unrealistic \· "Execute marketing campaign" → An activity, not a result \· ` · h4:Quantity Guidelines=`Company level: \· Objectives: 3-5 \· Key Results per O: 3-5 \·  \· Department level:` · h4:Alignment Verification=`Vertical alignment (Cascade): \· Company O → Department O → Team KR \·  \· Verification method: \· 1. If all department KRs are achieved, does the company KR get achieved?` · h4:Google Method (0.0 1.0)=`0.0-0.3: Failure — No meaningful progress \· 0.4-0.6: Progress — Significant effort, partial achievement \· 0.7: Success — Expected achievement level for a stretch goal \· 0.8-1.0: Over-achievement — Goal may have been too easy \· ` · h4:KR Progress Calculation=`Metric-based: \· Progress = (Current - Start) / (Target - Start) \· Example: NPS 40→60 target, currently 52 → (52-40)/(60-40) = 0.6 \·  \· Milestone-based:` · h3:OKR Anti-Patterns=`1. Disguising KPIs as OKRs \· "Maintain churn rate below 5%" → BAU metric, not an OKR \·  \· 2. Setting activities as KRs \· "Execute 3 marketing campaigns" → An activity, not a result` · h3:Verification Report Template=`## OKR Quality Verification Report \·  \· ### Quality Score by Objective \· \| O \| QSIM Score \| KR Count \| KR SMART-V \| Alignment \| \· `